            In the Minister's comments on Amendment No. 178, I understand him to be saying, "Yes, that is a good idea, but not just yet". The Minister looks doubtful as to whether he agrees, but I believe that he does. I am still surprised by that response, given that under many circumstances common sense alone would allow it to be said that a reservoir posed a very negligible risk. The noble Lord, Lord Dixon-Smith, described some of those circumstances. That is why I phrased my amendment as I did. A large but very shallow body of water, for the purposes that I outlined In my introduction, is unlikely to pose the sort of risk envisaged by the <a href="/acts/reservoirs-act-1975">Reservoirs Act</a>. I shall read his reply with interest and, perhaps, press him a little further on Report on what timescale the Government will need to arrive at a conclusion. In the meantime, I beg leave to withdraw the amendment.
