            The phrase,
            <q>fuel or field garden allotment",</q>
            means any allotment set out as a fuel allotment or a field garden allotment under an enclosure Act. That may refer to peat, or the noble Lord. Lord Palmer, may be about to come in and talk about biomass&#x2014;I know not. That is the answer that I can give the noble Lord. He may need further elucidation, as will I.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0647P0-03747'>
        <a name='S5LV0647P0_20030429_GCR_201'>  </a>
